WISE WORDS FROM...Robert S. Kaplan

"You don't have to put a dollar value on human capital to make it
comparable to inventory or accounts receivable. However, you do
want to quantify human capital; you do want to measure it in terms
that are appropriate for what you are accomplishing with the HR
function"

Robert S. Kaplan is a professor of Accounting and Control at Harvard
Business School, and his insights on linking strategy to HR are
invaluable. I strongly recommend HR professionals pay attention to
what Dr. Kaplan has to say.

http://www.hr.com/hrcom/clickthru/clickthru.cfm?linkid=1012731003

